---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout title="Pingmark Protocol | Invent2025">

    <header slot="header" class="h-20 flex items-center justify-between mb-8">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3 group">
            <img src="/assets/invent_2025_logo_icon.svg" alt="Invent2025 Logo"
                class="w-10 h-10 group-hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity">
            <div>
                <h1 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight font-mono">INVENT<span class="text-primary">2025</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-widest leading-none">Venture Studio</p>
            </div>
        </a>
        <div
            class="font-mono text-xs text-purple-400 border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-500/10 px-2 py-1 rounded">
            DRAFT SPECIFICATION v0.2
        </div>
    </header>

    <main>

        <div class="mb-12 text-center">
            <div
                class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto bg-purple-900/20 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center border border-purple-500/30 mb-6">
                <span class="font-mono text-4xl font-bold text-purple-400">!@</span>
            </div>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">The Pingmark Protocol</h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                A Universal Semantic Identifier for Physical Locations.
            </p>
        </div>

        <article
            class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none bg-surface-dark border border-border-dark p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl shadow-2xl relative overflow-hidden">
            <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 opacity-20">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-9xl">science</span>
            </div>

            <h3>Abstract</h3>
            <p>
                Current geolocation standards (GPS coordinates, Plus Codes) are designed for machines, not humans.
                They lack semantic context. Pingmark introduces a textual standard starting with the <code>!@</code>
                prefix (e.g., <code>!@starbucks.union-sq</code>) to allow humans to share precise location context
                across platforms.
            </p>

            <h3>Core Concept</h3>
            <p>
                Unlike DNS, Pingmark depends on a decentralized registry of spatial anchors.
            </p>

            <div
                class="not-prose bg-black/50 p-4 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm text-green-400 border border-border-dark my-6">
                !@brand.location.sub-location<br>
                !@hotel-hilton.lobby.desk-2
            </div>

            <h3>Applications</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Logistics:</strong> Precise drop-off points beyond street addresses.</li>
                <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Rapid semantic sharing of location context.</li>
                <li><strong>AR/VR:</strong> Anchoring digital content to physical semantic zones.</li>
            </ul>

        </article>

        <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center">
            <a href="https://pingmark.me" target="_blank"
                class="flex items-center gap-3 px-6 py-3 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 border border-slate-700 rounded-full transition-all">
                <span class="font-mono text-sm text-white">Read Full Whitepaper</span>
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-sm">open_in_new</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    </main>

    <footer slot="footer" class="mt-20 border-t border-border-dark pt-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs font-mono">Â© <span id="current-year">{currentYear}</span> Invent2025 Ltd.</p>
    </footer>

</Layout>
